This paper proposes a deep learning architecture for multi-label zero-shot learning, which is a task related to computer vision (CV) and artificial intelligence (AI). The model incorporates knowledge graphs, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL), suggesting that it may also be relevant to these sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions that the model can be applied to multi-modal (MM) tasks, further supporting the inclusion of cs.MM as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper focuses on the performance of the proposed method, suggesting that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
